Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Boil a full kettle.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pour the boiled water from your kettle into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat. Add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated).

Once the oven is hot, lay the @British Chicken Breasts{2} flat onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season, then rub in the @Mixed Herbs{1%sachet} and half the garlic. Put the @Asparagus{150%grams} on the other side of the baking tray, drizzle with oil, season, then toss to coat.

Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the chicken cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. 

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Return them to the pan, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cover with a lid to keep warm.

Trim the root and dark green leafy part from the @Leek{1}(trimmed) and discard. Halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large saucepan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the leek and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add the remaining garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{50%milliliter} into the leeks. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%grams}(grated) until melted. Taste the sauce and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

When ready, share the chicken thighs between your plates. Spoon over the cheesy leek sauce.

Serve with the mash alongside.

Enjoy!